<h1>Portobello Fajitas</h1>

<h2>Ingredients</h2>

<ul>
<li> 2 tablespoons olive oil </li>
<li> 1/4 teaspoon salt </li>
<li> 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper </li>
<li> 3 medium portobello mushrooms </li>
<li> 1 red and/or yellow sweet pepper, quartered </li>
<li> 8 6 inches flour tortillas (soft taco or fajita size) </li>
<li> 2 medium avocados, halved, seeded, and peeled </li>
<li> 1/4 cup light mayonnaise </li>
<li> 1 teaspoon chili powder </li>
<li> Salsa Verde </li>
<li> Fresh Cilantro sprigs </li>
<li> Lime wedges </li>
</ul>

<h2>Directions</h2>

<p>In a small bowl combine olive oil, salt, and pepper.</p>

<p>Brush the portobello mushrooms and sweet pepper with the olive oil mixture. Stack tortillas and wrap in foil.</p>

<p>For a charcoal grill, place the portobellos, pepper quarters, and foil packet on the rack of an uncovered grill directly over medium coals. Grill 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, turning once halfway through grilling time. (For a gas grill, preheat grill. Reduce heat the medium. Place portobellos, pepper quarters, and foil packet on a grill rack over heat. Cover and grill as above.)</p>

<p>Slice portobello and sweet pepper into strips. In a medium bowl, mash one of the avocados; stir in mayonnaise and chili powder. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Slice remaining avocado. Serve sweet pepper, portabello and sliced avocado on tortillas. Top with mayonnaise mixture. Makes 4 servings.</p>

